1/**



2 ******************************************************************************



3 * @file    stm32f4xx.h



4 * @author  MCD Application Team



5 * @version V1.7.0



6 * @date    22-April-2016



7 * @brief   CMSIS Cortex-M4 Device Peripheral Access Layer Header File.



8 *          This file contains all the peripheral register's definitions, bits



9 *          definitions and memory mapping for STM32F4xx devices.



10 *



11 *          The file is the unique include file that the application programmer



12 *          is using in the C source code, usually in main.c. This file contains:



13 *           - Configuration section that allows to select:



14 *              - The device used in the target application



15 *              - To use or not the peripheral’s drivers in application code(i.e.



16 *                code will be based on direct access to peripheral’s registers



17 *                rather than drivers API), this option is controlled by



18 *                "#define USE_STDPERIPH_DRIVER"



19 *              - To change few application-specific parameters such as the HSE



20 *                crystal frequency



21 *           - Data structures and the address mapping for all peripherals



22 *           - Peripherals registers declarations and bits definition



23 *           - Macros to access peripheral’s registers hardware



24 *



25 ******************************************************************************



26 * @attention



27 *



28 * <h2><center>&copy; COPYRIGHT 2016 STMicroelectronics</center></h2>



29 *



30 * Licensed under MCD-ST Liberty SW License Agreement V2, (the "License");



31 * You may not use this file except in compliance with the License.



32 * You may obtain a copy of the License at:



33 *



34 *        http://www.st.com/software_license_agreement_liberty_v2



35 *



36 * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software



37 * distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,



38 * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.



39 * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and



40 * limitations under the License.



41 *



42 ******************************************************************************



43 */

169  /**



170   * @brief STM32F4XX Standard Peripherals Library version number V1.7.0



171   */



172#define __STM32F4XX_STDPERIPH_VERSION_MAIN (0x01)                /*!< [31:24] main version */



173#define __STM32F4XX_STDPERIPH_VERSION_SUB1 (0x07)                /*!< [23:16] sub1 version */



174#define __STM32F4XX_STDPERIPH_VERSION_SUB2 (0x00)                /*!< [15:8]  sub2 version */



175#define __STM32F4XX_STDPERIPH_VERSION_RC (0x00)                  /*!< [7:0]  release candidate */



176#define __STM32F4XX_STDPERIPH_VERSION  ((__STM32F4XX_STDPERIPH_VERSION_MAIN << 24) |(__STM32F4XX_STDPERIPH_VERSION_SUB1 << 16) |(__STM32F4XX_STDPERIPH_VERSION_SUB2 << 8) |(__STM32F4XX_STDPERIPH_VERSION_RC))

189#define __CM4_REV                      0x0001                    /*!< Core revision r0p1                            */



190#define __MPU_PRESENT                  1                         /*!< STM32F4XX provides an MPU                     */



191#define __NVIC_PRIO_BITS               4                         /*!< STM32F4XX uses 4 Bits for the Priority Levels */



192#define __Vendor_SysTickConfig         0                         /*!< Set to 1 if different SysTick Config is used  */



193#define __FPU_PRESENT                  1                         /*!< FPU present                                   */

1777    __IO uint32_t CR;                  /*!< CRYP control register,                                    Address offset: 0x00 */



1778    __IO uint32_t SR;                  /*!< CRYP status register,                                     Address offset: 0x04 */



1779    __IO uint32_t DR;                  /*!< CRYP data input register,                                 Address offset: 0x08 */



1780    __IO uint32_t DOUT;                /*!< CRYP data output register,                                Address offset: 0x0C */



1781    __IO uint32_t DMACR;               /*!< CRYP DMA control register,                                Address offset: 0x10 */



1782    __IO uint32_t IMSCR;               /*!< CRYP interrupt mask set/clear register,                   Address offset: 0x14 */



1783    __IO uint32_t RISR;                /*!< CRYP raw interrupt status register,                       Address offset: 0x18 */



1784    __IO uint32_t MISR;                /*!< CRYP masked interrupt status register,                    Address offset: 0x1C */



1785    __IO uint32_t K0LR;                /*!< CRYP key left  register 0,                                Address offset: 0x20 */



1786    __IO uint32_t K0RR;                /*!< CRYP key right register 0,                                Address offset: 0x24 */



1787    __IO uint32_t K1LR;                /*!< CRYP key left  register 1,                                Address offset: 0x28 */



1788    __IO uint32_t K1RR;                /*!< CRYP key right register 1,                                Address offset: 0x2C */



1789    __IO uint32_t K2LR;                /*!< CRYP key left  register 2,                                Address offset: 0x30 */



1790    __IO uint32_t K2RR;                /*!< CRYP key right register 2,                                Address offset: 0x34 */



1791    __IO uint32_t K3LR;                /*!< CRYP key left  register 3,                                Address offset: 0x38 */



1792    __IO uint32_t K3RR;                /*!< CRYP key right register 3,                                Address offset: 0x3C */



1793    __IO uint32_t IV0LR;               /*!< CRYP initialization vector left-word  register 0,         Address offset: 0x40 */



1794    __IO uint32_t IV0RR;               /*!< CRYP initialization vector right-word register 0,         Address offset: 0x44 */



1795    __IO uint32_t IV1LR;               /*!< CRYP initialization vector left-word  register 1,         Address offset: 0x48 */



1796    __IO uint32_t IV1RR;               /*!< CRYP initialization vector right-word register 1,         Address offset: 0x4C */



1797    __IO uint32_t CSGCMCCM0R;          /*!< CRYP GCM/GMAC or CCM/CMAC context swap register 0,        Address offset: 0x50 */



1798    __IO uint32_t CSGCMCCM1R;          /*!< CRYP GCM/GMAC or CCM/CMAC context swap register 1,        Address offset: 0x54 */



1799    __IO uint32_t CSGCMCCM2R;          /*!< CRYP GCM/GMAC or CCM/CMAC context swap register 2,        Address offset: 0x58 */



1800    __IO uint32_t CSGCMCCM3R;          /*!< CRYP GCM/GMAC or CCM/CMAC context swap register 3,        Address offset: 0x5C */



1801    __IO uint32_t CSGCMCCM4R;          /*!< CRYP GCM/GMAC or CCM/CMAC context swap register 4,        Address offset: 0x60 */



1802    __IO uint32_t CSGCMCCM5R;          /*!< CRYP GCM/GMAC or CCM/CMAC context swap register 5,        Address offset: 0x64 */



1803    __IO uint32_t CSGCMCCM6R;          /*!< CRYP GCM/GMAC or CCM/CMAC context swap register 6,        Address offset: 0x68 */



1804    __IO uint32_t CSGCMCCM7R;          /*!< CRYP GCM/GMAC or CCM/CMAC context swap register 7,        Address offset: 0x6C */



1805    __IO uint32_t CSGCM0R;             /*!< CRYP GCM/GMAC context swap register 0,                    Address offset: 0x70 */



1806    __IO uint32_t CSGCM1R;             /*!< CRYP GCM/GMAC context swap register 1,                    Address offset: 0x74 */



1807    __IO uint32_t CSGCM2R;             /*!< CRYP GCM/GMAC context swap register 2,                    Address offset: 0x78 */



1808    __IO uint32_t CSGCM3R;             /*!< CRYP GCM/GMAC context swap register 3,                    Address offset: 0x7C */



1809    __IO uint32_t CSGCM4R;             /*!< CRYP GCM/GMAC context swap register 4,                    Address offset: 0x80 */



1810    __IO uint32_t CSGCM5R;             /*!< CRYP GCM/GMAC context swap register 5,                    Address offset: 0x84 */



1811    __IO uint32_t CSGCM6R;             /*!< CRYP GCM/GMAC context swap register 6,                    Address offset: 0x88 */



1812    __IO uint32_t CSGCM7R;             /*!< CRYP GCM/GMAC context swap register 7,                    Address offset: 0x8C */



1813  } CRYP_TypeDef;



1814



1815  /**



1816   * @brief HASH



1817   */



1818  typedef struct {



1819    __IO uint32_t CR;                  /*!< HASH control register,          Address offset: 0x00        */



1820    __IO uint32_t DIN;                 /*!< HASH data input register,       Address offset: 0x04        */



1821    __IO uint32_t STR;                 /*!< HASH start register,            Address offset: 0x08        */



1822    __IO uint32_t HR[5];               /*!< HASH digest registers,          Address offset: 0x0C-0x1C   */



1823    __IO uint32_t IMR;                 /*!< HASH interrupt enable register, Address offset: 0x20        */



1824    __IO uint32_t SR;                  /*!< HASH status register,           Address offset: 0x24        */



1825    uint32_t RESERVED[52];             /*!< Reserved, 0x28-0xF4                                         */



1826    __IO uint32_t CSR[54];             /*!< HASH context swap registers,    Address offset: 0x0F8-0x1CC */



1827  } HASH_TypeDef;

1830   * @brief HASH_DIGEST



1831   */

1833    __IO uint32_t HR[8];               /*!< HASH digest registers,          Address offset: 0x310-0x32C */



1834  } HASH_DIGEST_TypeDef;

2250#define ADC_SR_AWD                     ((uint8_t)0x01)           /*!<Analog watchdog flag               */

2257  /*******************  Bit definition for ADC_CR1 register  ********************/



2258#define ADC_CR1_AWDCH                  ((uint32_t)0x0000001F)    /*!<AWDCH[4:0] bits (Analog watchdog channel select bits) */



2259#define ADC_CR1_AWDCH_0                ((uint32_t)0x00000001)    /*!<Bit 0 */

2270#define ADC_CR1_DISCEN                 ((uint32_t)0x00000800)    /*!<Discontinuous mode on regular channels                */



2271#define ADC_CR1_JDISCEN                ((uint32_t)0x00001000)    /*!<Discontinuous mode on injected channels               */



2272#define ADC_CR1_DISCNUM                ((uint32_t)0x0000E000)    /*!<DISCNUM[2:0] bits (Discontinuous mode channel count)  */

10865  /* Bit definition for Ethernet MAC Control Register register */



10866#define ETH_MACCR_WD                   ((uint32_t)0x00800000)    /* Watchdog disable */



10867#define ETH_MACCR_JD                   ((uint32_t)0x00400000)    /* Jabber disable */



10868#define ETH_MACCR_IFG                  ((uint32_t)0x000E0000)    /* Inter-frame gap */



10869#define ETH_MACCR_IFG_96Bit            ((uint32_t)0x00000000)    /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 96Bit */



10870#define ETH_MACCR_IFG_88Bit            ((uint32_t)0x00020000)    /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 88Bit */



10871#define ETH_MACCR_IFG_80Bit            ((uint32_t)0x00040000)    /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 80Bit */



10872#define ETH_MACCR_IFG_72Bit            ((uint32_t)0x00060000)    /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 72Bit */



10873#define ETH_MACCR_IFG_64Bit            ((uint32_t)0x00080000)    /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 64Bit */



10874#define ETH_MACCR_IFG_56Bit            ((uint32_t)0x000A0000)    /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 56Bit */



10875#define ETH_MACCR_IFG_48Bit            ((uint32_t)0x000C0000)    /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 48Bit */



10876#define ETH_MACCR_IFG_40Bit            ((uint32_t)0x000E0000)    /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 40Bit */



10877#define ETH_MACCR_CSD                  ((uint32_t)0x00010000)    /* Carrier sense disable (during transmission) */



10878#define ETH_MACCR_FES                  ((uint32_t)0x00004000)    /* Fast ethernet speed */



10879#define ETH_MACCR_ROD                  ((uint32_t)0x00002000)    /* Receive own disable */



10880#define ETH_MACCR_LM                   ((uint32_t)0x00001000)    /* loopback mode */



10881#define ETH_MACCR_DM                   ((uint32_t)0x00000800)    /* Duplex mode */



10882#define ETH_MACCR_IPCO                 ((uint32_t)0x00000400)    /* IP Checksum offload */



10883#define ETH_MACCR_RD                   ((uint32_t)0x00000200)    /* Retry disable */



10884#define ETH_MACCR_APCS                 ((uint32_t)0x00000080)    /* Automatic Pad/CRC stripping */



10885#define ETH_MACCR_BL                   ((uint32_t)0x00000060)    /* Back-off limit: random integer number (r) of slot time delays before rescheduling



10886                                                                    a transmission attempt during retries after a collision: 0 =< r <2^k */



10887#define ETH_MACCR_BL_10                ((uint32_t)0x00000000)    /* k = min (n, 10) */



10888#define ETH_MACCR_BL_8                 ((uint32_t)0x00000020)    /* k = min (n, 8) */



10889#define ETH_MACCR_BL_4                 ((uint32_t)0x00000040)    /* k = min (n, 4) */



10890#define ETH_MACCR_BL_1                 ((uint32_t)0x00000060)    /* k = min (n, 1) */



10891#define ETH_MACCR_DC                   ((uint32_t)0x00000010)    /* Defferal check */



10892#define ETH_MACCR_TE                   ((uint32_t)0x00000008)    /* Transmitter enable */



10893#define ETH_MACCR_RE                   ((uint32_t)0x00000004)    /* Receiver enable */



10894



10895  /* Bit definition for Ethernet MAC Frame Filter Register */



10896#define ETH_MACFFR_RA                  ((uint32_t)0x80000000)    /* Receive all */



10897#define ETH_MACFFR_HPF                 ((uint32_t)0x00000400)    /* Hash or perfect filter */

10902#define ETH_MACFFR_PCF_ForwardAll      ((uint32_t)0x00000080)    /* MAC forwards all control frames to application even if they fail the Address Filter */



10903#define ETH_MACFFR_PCF_ForwardPassedAddrFilter ((uint32_t)0x000000C0) /* MAC forwards control frames that pass the Address Filter. */



10904#define ETH_MACFFR_BFD                 ((uint32_t)0x00000020)    /* Broadcast frame disable */



10905#define ETH_MACFFR_PAM                 ((uint32_t)0x00000010)    /* Pass all mutlicast */



10906#define ETH_MACFFR_DAIF                ((uint32_t)0x00000008)    /* DA Inverse filtering */

10909#define ETH_MACFFR_PM                  ((uint32_t)0x00000001)    /* Promiscuous mode */

10949  /* Bit definition for Ethernet MAC Remote Wake-UpFrame Filter Register */



10950#define ETH_MACRWUFFR_D                ((uint32_t)0xFFFFFFFF)    /* Wake-up frame filter register data */



10951



10952  /* Eight sequential Writes to this address (offset 0x28) will write all Wake-UpFrame Filter Registers.



10953     Eight sequential Reads from this address (offset 0x28) will read all Wake-UpFrame Filter Registers. */



10954  /* Wake-UpFrame Filter Reg0 : Filter 0 Byte Mask



10955     Wake-UpFrame Filter Reg1 : Filter 1 Byte Mask



10956     Wake-UpFrame Filter Reg2 : Filter 2 Byte Mask



10957     Wake-UpFrame Filter Reg3 : Filter 3 Byte Mask



10958     Wake-UpFrame Filter Reg4 : RSVD - Filter3 Command - RSVD - Filter2 Command -



10959     RSVD - Filter1 Command - RSVD - Filter0 Command



10960     Wake-UpFrame Filter Re5 : Filter3 Offset - Filter2 Offset - Filter1 Offset - Filter0 Offset



10961     Wake-UpFrame Filter Re6 : Filter1 CRC16 - Filter0 CRC16



10962     Wake-UpFrame Filter Re7 : Filter3 CRC16 - Filter2 CRC16 */



10963

11250#define ETH_DMAOMR_FUGF                ((uint32_t)0x00000040)    /* Forward undersized good frames */



11251#define ETH_DMAOMR_RTC                 ((uint32_t)0x00000018)    /* receive threshold control */



11252#define ETH_DMAOMR_RTC_64Bytes         ((uint32_t)0x00000000)    /* threshold level of the MTL Receive FIFO is 64 Bytes */



11253#define ETH_DMAOMR_RTC_32Bytes         ((uint32_t)0x00000008)    /* threshold level of the MTL Receive FIFO is 32 Bytes */



11254#define ETH_DMAOMR_RTC_96Bytes         ((uint32_t)0x00000010)    /* threshold level of the MTL Receive FIFO is 96 Bytes */



11255#define ETH_DMAOMR_RTC_128Bytes        ((uint32_t)0x00000018)    /* threshold level of the MTL Receive FIFO is 128 Bytes */



11256#define ETH_DMAOMR_OSF                 ((uint32_t)0x00000004)    /* operate on second frame */



11257#define ETH_DMAOMR_SR                  ((uint32_t)0x00000002)    /* Start/stop receive */



11258



11259  /* Bit definition for Ethernet DMA Interrupt Enable Register */



11260#define ETH_DMAIER_NISE                ((uint32_t)0x00010000)    /* Normal interrupt summary enable */



11261#define ETH_DMAIER_AISE                ((uint32_t)0x00008000)    /* Abnormal interrupt summary enable */



11262#define ETH_DMAIER_ERIE                ((uint32_t)0x00004000)    /* Early receive interrupt enable */



11263#define ETH_DMAIER_FBEIE               ((uint32_t)0x00002000)    /* Fatal bus error interrupt enable */



11264#define ETH_DMAIER_ETIE                ((uint32_t)0x00000400)    /* Early transmit interrupt enable */



11265#define ETH_DMAIER_RWTIE               ((uint32_t)0x00000200)    /* Receive watchdog timeout interrupt enable */



11266#define ETH_DMAIER_RPSIE               ((uint32_t)0x00000100)    /* Receive process stopped interrupt enable */



11267#define ETH_DMAIER_RBUIE               ((uint32_t)0x00000080)    /* Receive buffer unavailable interrupt enable */



11268#define ETH_DMAIER_RIE                 ((uint32_t)0x00000040)    /* Receive interrupt enable */



11269#define ETH_DMAIER_TUIE                ((uint32_t)0x00000020)    /* Transmit Underflow interrupt enable */



11270#define ETH_DMAIER_ROIE                ((uint32_t)0x00000010)    /* Receive Overflow interrupt enable */



11271#define ETH_DMAIER_TJTIE               ((uint32_t)0x00000008)    /* Transmit jabber timeout interrupt enable */



11272#define ETH_DMAIER_TBUIE               ((uint32_t)0x00000004)    /* Transmit buffer unavailable interrupt enable */



11273#define ETH_DMAIER_TPSIE               ((uint32_t)0x00000002)    /* Transmit process stopped interrupt enable */



11274#define ETH_DMAIER_TIE                 ((uint32_t)0x00000001)    /* Transmit interrupt enable */



11275



11276  /* Bit definition for Ethernet DMA Missed Frame and Buffer Overflow Counter Register */



11277#define ETH_DMAMFBOCR_OFOC             ((uint32_t)0x10000000)    /* Overflow bit for FIFO overflow counter */



11278#define ETH_DMAMFBOCR_MFA              ((uint32_t)0x0FFE0000)    /* Number of frames missed by the application */



11279#define ETH_DMAMFBOCR_OMFC             ((uint32_t)0x00010000)    /* Overflow bit for missed frame counter */



11280#define ETH_DMAMFBOCR_MFC              ((uint32_t)0x0000FFFF)    /* Number of frames missed by the controller */



11281



11282  /* Bit definition for Ethernet DMA Current Host Transmit Descriptor Register */



11283#define ETH_DMACHTDR_HTDAP             ((uint32_t)0xFFFFFFFF)    /* Host transmit descriptor address pointer */



11284



11285  /* Bit definition for Ethernet DMA Current Host Receive Descriptor Register */



11286#define ETH_DMACHRDR_HRDAP             ((uint32_t)0xFFFFFFFF)    /* Host receive descriptor address pointer */



11287



11288  /* Bit definition for Ethernet DMA Current Host Transmit Buffer Address Register */



11289#define ETH_DMACHTBAR_HTBAP            ((uint32_t)0xFFFFFFFF)    /* Host transmit buffer address pointer */



11290



11291  /* Bit definition for Ethernet DMA Current Host Receive Buffer Address Register */



11292#define ETH_DMACHRBAR_HRBAP            ((uint32_t)0xFFFFFFFF)    /* Host receive buffer address pointer */

11305  /** @addtogroup Exported_macro

11307   */



11308#define SET_BIT(REG, BIT)              ((REG) |= (BIT))



11309#define CLEAR_BIT(REG, BIT)            ((REG) &= ~(BIT))



11310#define READ_BIT(REG, BIT)             ((REG) & (BIT))



11311#define CLEAR_REG(REG)                 ((REG) = (0x0))



11312#define WRITE_REG(REG, VAL)            ((REG) = (VAL))



11313#define READ_REG(REG)                  ((REG))



11314#define MODIFY_REG(REG, CLEARMASK, SETMASK) WRITE_REG((REG), (((READ_REG(REG)) & (~(CLEARMASK))) | (SETMASK)))
